transcription.text:
Speaker 1: I called last month to cancel a prescription, and they just put it on hold, but I just got—

Speaker 2: A message that you're sending it out again.

Speaker 1: Can you check and make sure that's—

Speaker 2: Give me your phone number.

Speaker 1: My phone number is 903-559-7948.

Speaker 2: No, it's not that one.

Speaker 1: Give me your zip code.

Speaker 2: 75501.

Speaker 1: 03.

Speaker 2: 03, I mean.

Speaker 1: Sorry.

Speaker 2: And what's your first and last name?

Speaker 1: Alan Duffy.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Yes, go ahead.

Speaker 1: Okay, and I do see one of your orders that go out there, sir.

Speaker 2: Were you looking at just kind of order as needed going forward?

Speaker 1: You don't have to receive it this way.

Speaker 2: No, I called to cancel it, and he said if I canceled it, then I wouldn't be able to—

Speaker 1: Renew it if I did need it, but he would put it on suspend, or suspend it for like six—

Speaker 2: Months or something.

Speaker 1: Yeah, did you know who you spoke to?

Speaker 2: Because I don't even see that they did that.

Speaker 1: I don't know who I spoke to, but that's what they told me, that I could suspend it.

Speaker 2: Oh, yeah, well, yeah, you don't have anything coming out.

Speaker 1: No, the email might have just been an old email.

Speaker 2: You don't have anything coming out.

Speaker 1: It looks like you are out for six months here.

Speaker 2: You're out until July.

Speaker 1: Okay, so I did add to that, just ignore that message, and if that was delayed—

Speaker 2: If you ignore that message, you're put all the way out there until July.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All righty.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome, sir.

Speaker 1: You have a good day.
